{"/service/ndnp/az/batch_az_iotite_ver01/data/sn84020064/00542866391/1929112001/0005.xml":{"full_text":"DOUGLAS. ARIZONA.\nWindham Says Hoover Has Shaped a\nProgram That Merits the Support of\nEveryone; Suggests Congratulations\n\u201cAnnouncement from Washing\nton that President Hoover plans to\nthrow the influence of the federal\ngovernment into the effort to bring\nabout a general activity in improve\nment work is the most gratifying\nthing that has come to my notice\nfor a !on< time and is so much\nmore con nendable than to have\nr mer\u00b0 pronouncement of words\nfrom the president on hew sound\nhi believed business of the country\nsaid W. W. Windhajp. Doug\nlar igent for the Southern Pacific\nrailway yestetday. talking about the\nbusiness outlook. \"That is so im\npoitant to our section of the coun\ntry that I have felt all day it was a\nwise and proper course for the\nchamber of commerce to send the\npresident an enthusiastic telegram\nof congratulations upon his stand.\nI hope that the chamber may act\nyet and make known how heartily\npeople here approve the course.\u201d\nadded Mr. Windham.\nThe reference of the railroad man\nwas to the plan which has been\n^haoing in Washington to stim\nulate a great national campaign\nof improvement that will stabilize\nconditions by making certain the\noutlay of funds that will go toward\npurchase of materials and em\n^ployment of labor throughout the\ncountry. Mr. Windham pointed out\nthat Arizona has been \u201cwhite,\u201d\nviewed from its business activity for\nseveral months and that such a\npolicy would be the safest way to\nmake certain that conditions con\ntinue sound here.\n\u201cSuch a construction campaign\nas seems to be forming ought to\nbring much good to our state which\nhas been enjoying a splendid in\ndustrial health for a considerable\nperiod,\u201d said Mr. Windham. \u201cThere\nis a vast amount of work that our\nstate ought to do in road construc\ntion. There is. without doubt, a\nserious need for a housing program\nto be carried out. Here in Douglas\nwe need more homes, especially of\nthe modern type. There is a need\nlor building construction all over\nFOR REAL ECONOMY\nBuy Something Made of\nCOPPER\nCalumet Arizona\nMining Company\nDOUGLAS, ARIZONA\nOLD GOLD\nchanged the nation's smoking\nBEST'S\nTHE SMOKE SCREEN THAT\nKEEPS OUT THROAT.SCRATCH\nII i 11111 HHII i\nIIILMJ Illi\n11 I J i\n\nIi w I i\nJw s\nI g\nP. Lnrillard Co.. Em. 1760\nBetter tobaccos make them smoother and better with \u201cnot a cough in a carload\u2019\u2019\nOn your Radio. OLD GOLD\u2014PAI'L WHITEMAN HOI R. Paul Whiteman, with his complete orchestra, every Tuesday, 9 to 10 P. M., Eastern Standard Time\nthe state and if that were carried\nout now at a time when, as has\nbeen pointed cut by President\nHoover, money may be had at a\nfavorable rate, everybody would be\nmaking progress because it would\nmake certain a continuance of\nbusiness health and keep our labor\nprofitably employed. I sincerely\nhope that the chamber of commerce\nwill show its approval of this, to\nmy way of thinking, splendid policy\nof the president by speaking up and\nsaying to him \u2018That meets our\nheartiest approval. We are gird\nyou have taken action instead of\nmerely saying something that\nsounds good. We congratulate you.\nMr. President, and stand unitedly\nwith you in this plan.\u2019 Of course,\nsomeone might phrase it better\nthan that, but that suggests my\nview of what the chamber of com\nmerce ought to do. We owe it to\nthe president to let him know, in\na time like thus, that he has the\nsupport of the people he is trying\nto benefit by the program he pro\nposes.\u201d\nCurl Getting Is\nEasy, Declares\nThis Specialist\nDemonstrator Will Prove\nHis Point in Shop This\nEvening at 7 o\u2019clock.\n\u201cSome people still have the idea\nthat having a permanent wave is\na form of slow suicide, and we\nmerely want to snow what a simple\nprocess it is.\u201d was the comment of\nC. D. Harrington of the Palomar\nBeauty shop regarding the demon\nstration which is to be given at the\nPalomar shop on Tenth street this\nDOUGLAS DAILY DISPATCH, WEDNESDAY MORNING, NOVEMBER 20. 1929.\nMillionaire Aids Swindled Bank\nZ Hk fl?\nx r\nC. S. Mott, multi-millionaire vice president of General Motors, who put\nup more than $1,500,000 of his personal funds to cover stock mirket\nlosses by employes- of his Union Industrial Bank at Flint, Mich., where\n\u201cthe greatest bank defalcation in American history\u201d is said to have\ntaken place, is sho w A here in conference with H. R. Wilkin (right), the\nbank\u2019s new executive vice president and cashier. He came from Detroit\nto aid Mott who resumed his former position after others had resigned.\nInset is Prosecuting Attorney Charles D. Beagle of Flint, who is con\nducting an investigation into the bank\u2019s $3,500,000 shortage.\nevening between 7 and 9 o\u2019clock.\nMiss Mildred Anderson, an em\nployee of the Arizona Edison com\npany, will be the model for the\ndemonstration which will include\nthe entire process of permanent\nwaving in all detail.\nTomorrow night Miss Anderson\nwill again be the model for a dem\nonstration of the application of a\nfacial mask called the plastique\nmask. This demonstration will be\nheld at 7 o\u2019clock also.\nWe plan to give various demon\nstrations from time to time here\njust to show the public how sim\nple and effective these beauty oper\nations really are.\u201d declared Mr.\nHarrington who with his wife have\nrecently purchased the Palomar\nBeauty shop.\nThe Harringtons also own a shop i\nin Flagstaff, which is under their\nmanagement.\nPrior to the fire in the old Gads\nden hotel in 1928, the Palomar\nBeauty shop which .until recently\nwas owned by Mr. and^ Mrs. Paul\nJ. Holtry, then operated the busi-1\nness under the name of the Gads\nden Beauty shop. The parlors were I\nmoved to the present location about\na year ago and have since been\nknown as the Palomar Beauty shop.\nMr. and Mrs. Holtry now have a I\nshop at El Paso, Texas,\nPalomino Carried Booze\nBut He Is Held Because\nOf The Immigration Law\nSimon Palomino, who was ap\nprehended by the U. S. border pa\ntrol on last Friday when it is al\nleged he was carrying a jug in each\nhand, will be in the court of U. S.\nCommissioner H. C. Beumler this\nmorning for a hearing. It should\nbe understood here and now, that\nthere is no law against carrying a\njug in each hand. But the alleged\ninfraction of the law in this case\nrests upon the further allegation\nthat the jug which Palomino was\ncarrying in each hand was filled\nwith mescal, a deadly violation of\nthe prohibition law of the United\nStates in general and of Arizona in\n...BECAUSE YOU NEEDED\nA COUGH LESS CIGARETTE\nPlay the cold season safe. This is the season when\nyou'll especially appreciate OLD GOLD\u2019S freedom\nfrom throat-scratch. They are gentle to your\nthroat They give you smoothness, cleanliness\nand wonderful flavor. OLD GOLD\u2019S pure, specially\nblended tobacco soothes and pleases. Let it tell\nyou OLD GOLD'S story \u2014pleasure without penalty,\nwonderful flavor plus throat-ease. Change to\nOLD GOLD today. For this is OLD GOLD weather.\nparticular, wherefore the border\npatrol could not do otherwise than\ntake Palomino into custody and\nhasten him to the jail to be held\nfor hearing.\nThe specific charge against the\naccused in this instance is not a\nprohibition case but an infraction\nof the prohibition law but one\nagainst the immigration law so that\nthe outlook for Palomino\u2019s future\nis not what might be termed rosy.\nIf he should win on the alleged at\ntempt to evade the port and get\ninto this country in violation of the\nimmigration law, then he might be\nheld for allegedly attempting to\nsmuggle the liquor into the United\nStates and that in the background,\nhe still might be brought into\ncourt as an offender of the prohi\nbition law. Too bad. for Palomino.\nJust too bad.\n18 MINERS BURIED\nMONS, Belgium, Nov. 19\nEighteen miners were buried alive\nlate today in the Houssu colliery\nwhen a slight earthquake or ex\nplosion causey a cave-in. Rescue\ncrews were forking tonight in an\neffort to reach the entombed men.\nIs Your\nStomach\na \u201cGasser\u201d?\nExcessive gas in stomach and bowels\ndoesn\u2019t necessarily mean that your food\nIs at fault or that you have chronic\ndyspepsia. In most cases it results\nfrom gastric neurasthenia \u2014a purely\nnervous condition which disturbs the\nfunctional activity of the stomach.\nTaking medicine to digest the food ar\ntificially is a waste of time. What you\nueed is a remedy to correct the nerv\nous trouble and prevent the formation\nof abnormal gas.\nGo to your druggist and ask for a\npackage of Baalmann\u2019s Gas Tablets,\nwhich are prepared especially for this\nailment. See how quickly they will re\nlieve pent-up gas and all its distressing\nsymptoms, among which are pain\nabout the heart, palpitation, anxiety,\nshortness of breath, drowsiness after\neating, heartburn and a peculiar gnaw\ning feeling in the stomach. Genuine\nBaalmann\u2019s Gas Tablets can be ob\ntained at any good drug store. Price 11.\nFalse Partition in Gas Tank of Ford\nCar Hides Mescal Allegedly Carried\nBy Romero in Attempt to Cross Line\nAlfonso Momero. traveling in a,\nFord with a secret compartment in\nthe gas tank in which he is alleged\nto have been carrying mescal, is\n\u2019somewhere in Mexico.\u201d according\nto notation on the memorandum\nbooks of the U. S. customs service\nas the result of the apprehension of\nRomero and his Ford car at the port\nlate Monday. The car is still in\nthe custody of the customs service\nand the mescal is an exhibit in the\ncase, now reposing in the office of\nE. M. Specht, the deputy collector\nof U. S. customs in the federal\nbuilding. The whereabouts of Ro\nmero are unknown to the govern\nment inspectors and possibly will\ncontinue so indefinitely.\nRomero, It is alleged, was attempt\ning to cross the border with the\nsecret compartment of his gas tank\ncontaining one gallon of mescal\nwhen the insoectors \u201csmelled a\nmouse.\u201d Accordingly they started\ntheir careful examination of his car,\na \u00bbA eventually they discovered that\nIt j a SALE/\nNOVEMBER SHOE\nSALE\nWednesday, November 20th to Saturday, November 23rd\nOur November Shoe Sale is held to clear away our shelves of surplus stocks before\nthe Christmas buying starts. You can save money by buying your Shoes here\nduring these 4 days.\nMen\u2019s Shoes\nA\nMen\u2019s Oxfords in black and\ntan; specially priced (t*^ IE\nduring Sale at\nMen\u2019s Oxfords in calf, kid\nand patent leather; specially\npriced during Sale $4.65\nat\nMen\u2019s High Shoes in black\nand tan, in calf or kid; spe\ncially priced during $3.95\n^ale at\nBoys\u2019 Oxfords in black and\ntan, sizes 2^2 to 6; specially\npriced during Sale $2.95\nBoys\u2019 High Shoes in black\ncalf, sizes 2 1-2 to 5 1-2; spe\ncially priced during Cl QE\nSale at\nBoy\u2019s Scout Bals with compo\nsition soles, sizes 9*/o to 2;\nspecially priced dur- Cl QC\ning Sale at T\n1\nROLLINS\u2019 SILK\nHOSE\nSI.OO\n$1.50\n$1.95\none end had been removed for some\nreason. Then they began to ex\namine the part of the tank from\nwhich the end had been cut and\nsoon made the further discovery\nthat there was a partition in the\ntank not usually found in gas tanks.\nSo they looked further for the an\nswer and located two openings\nthrough which the contents could\nbe removed and upon that discov\nery they found that the contents\nwere not pas but mescal. Then they\nbegan to look for the owner of\ncar but he was gone. It was then\nascertained that he had not waited\nfor all the discoveries to be made\nby the inspectors but had passed\nhurriedly through the port gate go\ning into Mexico and since then\nthere has been no trace obtained\nof the missing Romero.\nThe U. S. customs service is tak\ning good care of the Ford car and\nthe inspectors would be glad to i